article.headline: Littles' career-high 33 carry Virginia past Louisiana Tech
article.linkText: Littles leads Virginia to Cavalier Classic crown
article.story:
CHARLOTTESVILLE -- Lyndra Littles scored a career-high 33 points to lead Virginia (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 16 AP) to a 68-52 victory over Louisiana Tech in the championship game of the Cavalier Classic on Monday night.

It was the fifth straight title for the Cavaliers (11-2) and 20th in 23 years of the tournament.

Leading 15-14, Virginia used a 13-2 run over the next 5 minutes to take control of the game. The Cavaliers led 35-20 at the half and Louisiana Tech could only close to within 11 in the second half.

Adrienne Johnson led Tech (7-6) with 12 points. Leading scorer Shanavia Dowdell was plagued by foul trouble and finished with 11.

In the consolation game, UMBC beat Rider 76-55.
